            RENDERED IMAGE at 3x on BOTH revisions before claiming it, because this is exactly the
            class of thing a text layer invents (it was first spotted as a suspicious text-layer
            string, and the render is what upgraded it from suspicion to fact).
            ⇒ Pattern 10 is RIGHT and this is its edge, worth stating so a future session does not
            over-read it: THE PUBLISHER'S CURRENT COPY IS AUTHORITATIVE ABOUT WHAT IS CURRENT. IT IS
            NOT AUTOMATICALLY THE BETTER DOCUMENT. Newer is not a synonym for correct. Both copies are
            kept in the audit table for this reason.
            METHOD, and it cost a call: the se.com URL this project carried as the manufacturer's copy
            is a LANDING PAGE, not the document. It returns HTTP 200 and 138 KB of text/html with the
